{"name":"Artifact Specialist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have a knack for architecture and ancient crafting techniques. With a reasonable period of examination you can reconstruct the history of an item or structure, starting with the most recent happenings and ending with knowing the culture and era in which the item or structure was created. This takes several minutes for a small item, several days for a sprawling palace, and perhaps longer if the item or structure is severely damaged or altered from it's original form - at the DMs discretion.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FJkRHfYG3P4DTeOW"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1665863377150,"modifiedTime":1665863417974,"lastModifiedBy":"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"EHoW2cMhtyy9qtHU"}
{"name":"Information Dealer","type":"background","img":"modules/Gioppo/icons/Features/backgrounds/deler.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are an individual who collects, buys, sells, and trades information in order to make a living. Sifting through gossip for kernels of truth, mining tips from people in the know, and working your knuckles to the bone in the rumor mill to glean secrets are all the kinds of activities you might engage in to gather information. And once you have it, you trade that information to those who find it useful or valuable.</p><p>You may get other information in return for your trouble, though goods, services, favors, or even cold hard cash are just as often exchanged for the knowledge you deal in.</p><p>Regardless of how you get it or what you trade for it, dealing in information is your specialty, and there seems to always be a demand for such a service.</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies</strong>: History, Insight</p><p><strong>Languages</strong>: Two of your choice</p><p><strong>Equipment</strong>: A notebook, an ink pen, a dozen small tubes and slips of paper (for clandestine notes), a set of traveler’s clothes, and a pouch containing 15 gp.</p><p><strong>Feature</strong>: Informant Network</p><p>Given that your stock and trade is information, you have a respectable network of individuals spread across the territory you operate in. These informants don’t work for free, but they actively keep their eyes and ears open for information, rumors, and secrets at all times because they know that any intelligence they gather might potentially be valuable to you, and for many of them, this part of the business helps them line their pockets or accumulate favors.</p><p>When you are in search of information or rumors, you may reach out to your informant network. The GM will let you know what methods are permissible for this, and it is up to the GM’s discretion if and how your attempt succeeds, as well as what it might cost you. GMs are encouraged to use this feature to introduce plot hooks, hints, and world-building details to the player character.</p><p>Additionally, if someone knows that you are an information dealer, they may be inclined to do business with you (buying, selling, or otherwise) in exchange for information when they otherwise may not even consider it. This is entirely up to the GM’s discretion in any given situation, but it is possible that people you run across may be willing to buy or sell information through you in various capacities.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.sFyaOCAslqX5xtk6"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1682788427980,"modifiedTime":1682788837391,"lastModifiedBy":"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"MddMIn44kZwiWQRE"}
{"name":"Relic Hunter","type":"background","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>It's there, under our feet. Another place, a bygone era full of glory and beauty, moldering and forgotten. Not everyone passes these fallen monuments by. You are one of them - a documenter of lost lore, a finder of precious historical record and artifacts from times long gone - whether fallen golden ages or reminders of wars so titanic that they reshaped the world and gave birth to legends.</p><p>What drives you to brave the dangers of ancient ruins and crumbling reliquaries? Do you hunger to know what brought down the peace and prosperity of a dead empire?</p><p>Do you seek the knowledge of the ancients to understand the secrets of their power, their almost unfathomable magic? Or is your interest in the relics and art you recover centered on their value on the open market? Whatever your motivation, you combine a deep knowledge of history with derring-do and courage, things sorely needed to face the dangers involved in uncovering the past.</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies</strong>: History, Athletics</p><p><strong>Languages</strong>: Two languages of your choice.</p><p><strong>Equipment</strong>: Several sets of sturdy travelers attire, a single scholarly outfit, an intriguing treasure map of dubious authenticity, a belt pouch or purse with 15 gp.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[{"_id":"FaZGA0DmvsOmji4n","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.Gioppo.backgrounds.EHoW2cMhtyy9qtHU"],"optional":false,"spell":null},"value":{},"level":1}]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.73hlEMqhbCKKIXM6"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1665863078146,"modifiedTime":1665863453999,"lastModifiedBy":"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"SXR86ujAFOiERPsO"}
{"name":"Grim Determination","type":"feat","img":"modules/Gioppo/icons/Features/backgrounds/grim.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are used to having to push yourself to the limit to survive, and you know how to get the same out of your companions. When traveling for at least one entire day, you and up to five companions can spend an extra hour traveling each day without risk of exhaustion.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Survivor background","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.R1OGLCBKdxWFE9yV"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1663513656086,"modifiedTime":1682784745074,"lastModifiedBy":"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Tj85Pgi0mbZa0tVz"}
{"name":"Survivor","type":"background","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Life is dangerous in the worlds of D&amp;D, and the danger is not restricted solely to the lives of adventurers. At some point in your past, you narrowly avoided death in some sort of major event, and probably spent a good deal of time injured and alone before finally reaching safety or being rescued. Your life has been different ever since.</p><p>Skill Proficiencies: Medicine, Survival</p><p>Tool Proficiencies: Herbalism kit</p><p>Languages: One of your choice</p><p>Equipment: A healer’s kit, a memento of a deceased loved one, a set of traveler’s clothes, and a pouch containing 10 gp</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.Gioppo.backgrounds.Tj85Pgi0mbZa0tVz]{Grim Determination}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Unfortunate Origins","advancement":[{"_id":"4wnStTPQC9raMijX","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.Gioppo.backgrounds.Tj85Pgi0mbZa0tVz"],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":0,"title":"","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Zmj2V6xp7b21vi5E"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.2","coreVersion":"10.285","createdTime":1663514055897,"modifiedTime":1663514212959,"lastModifiedBy":"f2IZW0g7Izm7U70S"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"cCEufUdMOYnSRDWo"}
{"name":"Criminal","type":"background","img":"modules/Gioppo/icons/Features/criminal.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Proficiencies</strong>: Deception, Stealth, a gaming set, Thieves Tools</p><p><strong>Equipment</strong>: Crowbar, Dark common clothes with a hood, 15gp</p><p><strong>Criminal Contact.</strong> You have a contact who acts as a liaison to a network of other criminals. You know how to get messages to and from them, even at great distances.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"Xr1u3V90PlQMuvj3":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.38B1zYgV7HVrTiP2"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685049344134,"modifiedTime":1685049509625,"lastModifiedBy":"Xr1u3V90PlQMuvj3"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"rlkmD9LsFLHZzEBK"}
{"name":"Metal Worker","type":"background","img":"modules/Gioppo/icons/Features/backgrounds/smith.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You grew up with a hammer in your hand and fire at your back. Having grown up with the business of metalcraft as a constant, you are very learned in the ways of metal mining, smelting, casting, forging, and finishing, even if you are not necessarily personally practiced in those various crafts. With swarf under your heels, and clinker under your nails, you have endured the heat and choking smoke of metal shops for years. Your hands are calloused, and your body has adapted to be quite sturdy to accommodate the labor. Your body holds a record of every lesson hard learned, in the form of scars from various burns and scaldings, infections from metal slivers, cuts from scrap, friction burns from grinding wheels, and more. Metalworkers are tough, hard people, as if they are stone made flesh, and hold an important place in society somewhat outside of the traditional social hierarchy, because all of civilization depends on their artistry.</p><p>Discuss the circumstances of your experience with your DM. Were you an apprentice to a blacksmith, or did you teach yourself the ways of the forge? What types of weapons are your specialty? Why did you choose the gritty path of metalwork? What was your role in the forge - apprentice, designer, forger, salesperson, or some other role? Who was you mentor? Were you interned in a local shop, or perhaps you sought guidance from dwarvish masters themselves?</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies</strong>: Athletics, Insight</p><p><strong>Tool Proficiencies</strong>: Smith's tools</p><p><strong>Languages</strong>: Dwarvish or one other standard language of those who taught you</p><p><strong>Equipment</strong>: A set of smith's tools, a sledge hammer, a merchant's scale, a set of common clothes, a work apron, a pair of elbow-length leather gloves, an eye patch, and a belt pouch containing 15 gp</p><p><strong>Feature</strong>: Knowledge of the Trade</p><p>You can start and keep a roaring fire with ease, and can arrange materials to concentrate the heat in a fire, as if it were a forge. You know and recognize all manner of metalworking tools, and can recognize when an area has been used as part of a metalworking operation. You can identify geological features created by mining, such as yellow boy, slag heaps, tailings, and spoil tips. You can also assess the quality of a metal object from its color, feel, weight, and (if you worked with steel or brass) sound, and you can use this knowledge to identify frauds and assess value. You know how to care for metals such as to protect them from corroding as easily from normal use. You have advantage on any skill checks relating to crafting an item that relates to the specialization you chose.</p><p></p><p></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gsvqZcIO0cBv1l0y"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1682787432231,"modifiedTime":1682788334691,"lastModifiedBy":"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"shcVSYsExFSLhhnV"}
{"name":"Outlander","type":"background","img":"modules/Gioppo/icons/Features/backgrounds/outlander.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Proficiencies</strong>: Athletics, Survival, a Musical Instrument</p><p><strong>Language</strong>: One of your choice</p><p><strong>Equipment</strong>: Staff, hunting trap, trophy from an animal, travellers clothes, 10gp</p><p><strong>Wanderer</strong>. Excellent memory for maps and geography.</p><p>You are able to find food and freshwater for you and up to 5 other people each day, assuming the nearby land is able to support it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.sWQel3shB3kYsOTD"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1682784360215,"modifiedTime":1682784490809,"lastModifiedBy":"4eArs1l9WtlXTHwx"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"zhE6Zxrg2Ury5HQq"}
{"name":"Doctor","type":"background","flags":{"beavers-crafting":{"subtype":""},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vrilmXAsN0mRnalQ"}},"img":"modules/Gioppo/icons/Features/doctor.png","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are trained as a healer and a medical practitioner who makes a living by treating and/or studying diseases, maladies, and injuries. Most doctors typically intend to heal such conditions, though there are some who are more concerned with research and study than actually helping people.</p><p>Whatever your priorities, your background is characterized by the medical knowledge you picked up as you plied your trade as a doctor.</p><p>Skill Proficiencies: Medicine, Nature</p><p>Tool Proficiencies: Herbalism Kit</p><p>Languages: One of your choice</p><p>Equipment: A healing kit, a small knife or scalpel, a notebook and pencils, a set of common clothes, and a pouch containing 5 gp.</p><h3>Feature: Housecalls</h3><p>As a doctor, you are likely to find many opportunities to ply your trade as you go about your adventures. In particular, as you journey, you are likely to come upon populated villages, towns, cities, encampments, or even isolated hermitages.</p><p>These congregations are almost always in need of a doctor’s attention, especially the isolated or overpopulated ones.</p><p>People get sick and hurt; it is inevitable. So with no shortage of aches, pains, maladies, illnesses, and injuries, there is virtually always a demand for the services of a doctor wherever people dwell. If people are aware that you are an experienced doctor, they may try to convince you to help them. This convincing may simply involve mundane persuasion or coercion, but it may also come in the form of offered payments. Payments, of course, could mean money, special items, information, or any number of other useful/ valuable (or not) things. In certain places, some might even attempt to commandeer your services with varying degrees of guilt and/or force, so it may not always be a good idea to advertise your profession.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","advancement":[]},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"Xr1u3V90PlQMuvj3":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685290181530,"modifiedTime":1685290453805,"lastModifiedBy":"Xr1u3V90PlQMuvj3"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"ziRcu0YElZrHBEob"}
